---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { routes } from '../i18n/routes';
---
<Base
  lang="en"
  pageId="home"
  title="CarveTrace — Cryptographic EU AI Act evidence your auditor can re-verify without trusting us"
  description="Self-hosted Article 12 + 14 evidence platform. Every AI decision and human-oversight event bound at write-time as a single signed atom. Your auditor verifies the bundle in their browser without an account. Verifier free + open-source ; Starter from €15K/yr."
>
  <section class="hero hero--home">
    <p class="eyebrow">EU AI Act · Article 12 + 14 evidence</p>
    <h1>Evidence your auditor can re-verify — without trusting us.</h1>
    <p class="hero__lead">
      CarveTrace is the only EU AI Act evidence layer whose verdict survives
      the vendor. Every AI decision and the human oversight that reviewed it
      are bound at write-time as a single signed atom. Your auditor opens
      <a href="https://verify.carvetrace.com" rel="noopener">verify.carvetrace.com</a>,
      drops your bundle, and gets VERIFIED in seconds — open-source verifier,
      no account, no CarveTrace involvement.
    </p>
    <div class="hero__ctas">
      <a class="cta cta--primary" href="https://verify.carvetrace.com" rel="noopener">Open the verifier (free, no signup)</a>
      <a class="cta cta--ghost" href={routes.demo.en}>See the demo</a>
      <a class="cta cta--ghost" href={routes.contact.en}>Talk to us</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Deadlines strip — turns the rest of the page from "interesting" to
       "now". 47 days from June 17 to Aug 2 ; 175 days to Dec 9. -->
  <section class="home-deadlines">
    <h2 class="home-section__lead">Two deadlines moving 2026 AI compliance budget</h2>
    <div class="home-deadlines__grid">
      <article class="home-deadline">
        <p class="home-deadline__date">Aug 2, 2026</p>
        <h3>EU AI Act high-risk bind</h3>
        <p>
          Article 12 (record-keeping) and Article 14 (human oversight) enforceable.
          Fines up to €35M / 7% global turnover.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="home-deadline">
        <p class="home-deadline__date">Dec 9, 2026</p>
        <h3>PLD applies to AI</h3>
        <p>
          Product Liability Directive 2024/2853 extends strict liability +
          defect presumption to AI. The burden of disclosure shifts to the
          producer.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="panels">
    <article class="card">
      <p class="eyebrow">The problem</p>
      <h2>Most evidence dies with the vendor</h2>
      <p>
        Every AI governance platform — CredoAI, OneTrust, IBM watsonx.governance,
        Holistic AI — stores your evidence in their database and shows it to your
        auditor via their dashboard. If they go bankrupt, get subpoenaed, or
        suffer a tenant breach, your AI Act compliance defense goes with them.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <p class="eyebrow">The wedge</p>
      <h2>Cryptographic binding, your custody</h2>
      <p>
        CarveTrace is the only EU AI Act tool whose verifier runs in the
        auditor's browser, Apache 2.0, no account, no API key. The Article 12
        record and the Article 14 oversight event are bound by cryptographic
        hash at write-time — a single signed atom. <a href={routes.why.en}>Read the
        comparison ↗</a>
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <p class="eyebrow">The control</p>
      <h2>Self-hosted, EU-domiciled, your keys</h2>
      <p>
        CarveTrace runs on your infrastructure across every tier. We never see
        your data. Aryamind SARL is a French company — native EU residency, signed
        DPA + SCCs Module 2 + EU sub-processors. Your producer signing keys stay
        with you. The cryptography is the trust, not us.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>

  <!-- Pricing snippet ; self-qualification matters for a founder-led ABM
       motion. Prospects know if they're at "Starter" vs "Enterprise"
       without a sales call. -->
  <section class="home-pricing">
    <h2 class="home-section__lead">Priced by the unit the regulation regulates</h2>
    <p class="home-section__sublead">
      Per high-risk AI system × decision volume. Self-hosted across every
      tier. EUR, excluding VAT.
    </p>
    <div class="home-pricing__grid">
      <article class="home-pricing__tier">
        <h3>Verifier</h3>
        <p class="home-pricing__price"><strong>€0</strong>/forever</p>
        <p>Public WASM verifier, open-source. Try it now.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="home-pricing__tier">
        <h3>Starter</h3>
        <p class="home-pricing__price"><strong>€15K</strong>/year</p>
        <p>1 high-risk system, ≤500K decisions/yr.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="home-pricing__tier home-pricing__tier--featured">
        <h3>Growth</h3>
        <p class="home-pricing__price"><strong>€45K</strong>/year</p>
        <p>Up to 5 systems, ≤5M decisions/yr, SSO, DPA + EU residency.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="home-pricing__tier">
        <h3>Enterprise</h3>
        <p class="home-pricing__price"><strong>From €90K</strong></p>
        <p>Unlimited systems, ISO 42001 pack, dedicated CSM, DORA fit.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
    <div class="hero__ctas">
      <a class="cta cta--primary" href={routes.pricing.en}>See pricing detail</a>
      <a class="cta cta--ghost" href={routes.deck.en}>Read the 10-slide pitch</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Trust signals row — reads-mounted from the trust + status + docs work. -->
  <section class="home-trust">
    <h2 class="home-section__lead">Everything procurement asks for, pre-published</h2>
    <div class="home-trust__grid">
      <a class="home-trust__card" href={routes.trust.en}>
        <h3>Trust center →</h3>
        <p>Security, status, privacy, terms, DPA, license matrix, vendor questionnaires.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="home-trust__card" href={routes.dpa.en}>
        <h3>DPA pre-signed →</h3>
        <p>SCCs Module 2 incorporated. 48-hour breach notice. Sub-processor list.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="home-trust__card" href={routes.docs.en}>
        <h3>30+ docs →</h3>
        <p>Architecture, AI Act mapping, threat model, deployment guides — versioned with the code.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="home-trust__card" href={routes.blog.en}>
        <h3>Long reads →</h3>
        <p>Article 12 line-by-line. Article 14 evidence gaps. PLD burden-shift in 2026.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero--home { padding-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .hero__lead {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    max-width: 48rem;
  }
  .hero__lead a {
    color: var(--brand-600);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  .hero__ctas { margin-top: 1.5rem; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  .home-section__lead {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
    color: var(--ink-default);
  }
  .home-section__sublead {
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 50rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
  }

  /* Deadlines strip */
  .home-deadlines {
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
  }
  .home-deadlines__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(100%, 18rem), 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .home-deadline {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #fafafa 0%, #f4f4f5 100%);
    border: 1px solid var(--edge-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--brand-600);
  }
  .home-deadline__date {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--brand-600);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .home-deadline h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
  }
  .home-deadline p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Pricing snippet */
  .home-pricing { margin: 3rem 0; }
  .home-pricing__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(100%, 14rem), 1fr));
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .home-pricing__tier {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--edge-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  }
  .home-pricing__tier--featured {
    border-color: var(--brand-600);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(5, 150, 105, 0.08);
  }
  .home-pricing__tier h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem 0;
    color: var(--ink-default);
  }
  .home-pricing__price {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem 0;
  }
  .home-pricing__price strong {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--ink-default);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .home-pricing__tier p:last-child {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Trust signals */
  .home-trust { margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; }
  .home-trust__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(100%, 16rem), 1fr));
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .home-trust__card {
    display: block;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--edge-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: border-color 150ms ease, box-shadow 150ms ease;
  }
  .home-trust__card:hover {
    border-color: var(--brand-600);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(5, 150, 105, 0.08);
  }
  .home-trust__card h3 {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem 0;
    color: var(--ink-default);
  }
  .home-trust__card p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
